Thinly slice the fillets and then cut them into Â¾-inch squares. Cover and refrigerate while you prepare the rest of the recipe. Put four small serving bowls in the refrigerator to chill. For the marinade dressing Combine all the ingredients in a bowl. Set the bowl inside a larger one filled with ice while you prepare the salad. For the Salad In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, onion, cilantro, cumin, and salt and pepper. In a larger bowl, toss the vinaigrette with the avocado and jicama. Refrigerate. To finish the dish Add the sea bass to the marinade/dressing and gently mix. Let stand for about 10 minutes. Spoon the ceviche, with its liquid, into the four chilled bowls. Serve with the salad, and encourage your guests to top their ceviche with salad.